    <div class="col-md-12">
        <p> We made our way back to the hotel. Make it chic quickly, because today is Christmas and you give yourself a little. Since we are not at home this year, we decided to give ourselves a nice joint experience for Christmas. We gave each other tickets for the Harlem Gospel Choir in the Sony Hall on Broadway. On the way there we passed another Christmas market and take the chance to stroll over it. </p>
        <p> As I said, the concert was in the Sony Music Hall. What turned out to be a kind of restaurant with a stage. We were there in good time that we got a nice somewhat increase space with a good view. About 20 rows sat in front of us, which didn't bother at all. Since only the loudspeakers were switched on directly on the stage, the music was not too loud for us, so that I could even enjoy the concert this time without hearing protection. After about an hour the choir took a short break. Steffi took the chance to kick off. A few minutes later she comes back with a grin and tells that left and right next to her was sung in the cabins. When she got out, she found that the singers were personally. The remaining women from the choir stood in the queue to the toilets. They have to go where too. The concert went for a total of 2 hours and the choir obviously had fun on stage and included the audience on the show. After the concert, all singers were still at the exit and were available for conversations, photos and signatures. </p>
        <p> After that we went back to the hotel. It was already after 10 p.m. and tomorrow our train will go to Washington D.C. </p>
